**Overall Meaning:**

"May my mind be filled with auspicious thoughts, by whom this universe, the world, became, those gods also, the great knowers of the born, that very fire, the light of darkness, the one light."

**Explanation:**

This verse highlights the divine as the ultimate source of creation and knowledge.  It describes the divine as the force that brought forth the universe, the gods, and all beings.  The verse also refers to the divine as "fire," symbolizing its transformative power and its ability to illuminate the darkness of ignorance.  It emphasizes that this divine fire, or light, is the one source of all reality, transcending the duality of darkness and light. The verse expresses a desire for the mind to be filled with thoughts that are aligned with this ultimate truth. 
